Sentencas: This paper reports the fabrication of the SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+delta (SBSCO) infiltrated scandia-stabilized-zirconia (SSZ) composite cathode for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs).
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effects of the calcination temperature on the structure, morphology and polarization resistance of the composite cathode were studied.
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Cathode calcinated at 700 degrees C showed the finest microstructure and the lowest polarization resistance, e.g., 0.054 and 0.172 Omega cm(2) at 700 and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal shock resistance of the composite cathode was studied and no degradation was found after the 35 thermal cycles conducted between 100 and 600 degrees C with a rate of 10 degrees C min (1).
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: MS-SOFC with the SBSCO infiltrated SSZ cathode
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: was prepared and the maximum power density (MPD) can be as high as 1.25, 0.92, 0.61 and 0.39 W cm (2) when measured at 700, 650, 600 and 550 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Infiltrated SmBa0.5Sr0.5Co2O5+δ cathodes for metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
